        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 8 at 8:29PM EDT until May 8 at 9:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Mecklenburg County in the Piedmont of North
Carolina...
Southeastern Gaston County in the Piedmont of North Carolina...
Northeastern York County in Upstate South Carolina...

* Until 915 PM EDT.

* At 829 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles northeast
of York, or 4 miles east of Clover, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Steele Creek, Clover, Tega Cay, Carowinds, Lake Wylie, Fort Mill,
Newport, Southwest Charlotte, Charlotte Douglas Airport, and Rock
Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows!

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or Tweet it using hashtag nwsgsp. Your
message should describe the event and the specific location where it
occurred.</instruction>
